                              <list>
                                 <item xml:id="q1" n="1">
                                    <dim unit="leaf">6</dim>
                                    <locus from="1" to="6"/></item>
                                 <note>all folia are disjoined except the bifolium 2-3: this first quire is difficult to reconstruct, 
                                    because at least one initial folium is lost, but probably two or even three folia are missing; moreover, one folium is lost between ff. 5 and 6. A possible reconstruction would be: I10(-4: i, ii, iii, ix), 
                                    that is a quinion with loss of folia in the first, second, third, and ninth positions. It is clear that extant ff. 2–3 are the central bifolium of the quire and ff. 1–4 are also one bifolium. 
                                    The missing portion of the first text, the Ecclesiastical canons, would probably need only one folium, which means that the first two folia were occupied by a further text that is lost. 
                                    One could surmise that an introductory text or a table of content of the collection occupied this place.</note>
